are, software, and content that help people feel connected, as well as Meta Quest devices that enable social experiences across gaming, fitness, entertainment, and more. The segment also includes wearables such as AI glasses like Ray Ban Meta and Oakley Meta glasses; and the Meta Ray Ban Display, which combines AI glasses with an integrated lens display and the Meta Neural Band, a wrist worn device using electromyography that lets people control their AI glasses through neuromuscular signals. Meta Platforms, Inc. has a collaboration with Microsoft Corporation, NVIDIA Corporation, Advanced Micro Devices, Inc., Broadcom Inc., and OpenAI, L.L.C. The company was formerly known as Facebook, Inc. and changed its name to Meta Platforms, Inc. in October 2021. The company was incorporated in 2004 and is headquartered in Menlo Park, California.","sharesOutstanding":2196045588}},{"id":"f9ace828-9d5b-4b33-9947-0dc741d2f008","ticker":"NTAP","company_name":"NetApp, Inc.","sector":"Technology","country":"United States","current_price":114.19,"daily_change_pct":-3.0068801494946116,"low52":93.69,"high52":126.66,"setup_type":"consensus_buy","graham_decision":"BUY","market_decision":"BUY","graham_confidence":"High","market_confidence":"High","graham_thesis":"Fortress profitability (150% ROIC, 70% gross margin) at fair valuation (P/E 19.7脙聴, forward 13.8脙聴) with net cash and 28% margin of safety.","market_thesis":"EPS growth 20% with forward P/E 13.8脙聴 signals undervalued momentum and multiple expansion runway.","insight":"Graham and the market agree 芒聙聰 both sides see an opportunity.","score":120,"situation_type":"value_opportunity","scanned_at":"2026-05-12T17:00:07.047881+00:00","is_featured":false,"full_analysis":{"ai":{"verdict":"waiting","moatType":"None","questions":[],"moatRating":"None","missingFactors":null,"catalystPresent":false,"grahamNarrative":"","positiveSignals":[],"catalystTimeline":null,"verdictReasoning":"","indicatorInsights":{},"challengingSignals":[],"problemExpla