 developers to build custom applications. The company serves the professional and business services, financial services, healthcare, manufacturing, media, education, government, technology, media, retail, and hospitality industries. It sells its solutions through its direct sales organization. The company was formerly known as North Tahoe Power Tools, Inc. and changed its name to Workday, Inc. in July 2005. Workday, Inc. was incorporated in 2005 and is headquartered in Pleasanton, California.","sharesOutstanding":203712072}},{"id":"c194fc4d-ceff-4822-be0b-6307ac9a3b86","ticker":"PTC","company_name":"PTC Inc.","sector":"Technology","country":"United States","current_price":144.72,"daily_change_pct":-0.8223684210526239,"low52":130.89,"high52":219.69,"setup_type":"consensus_buy","graham_decision":"BUY","market_decision":"BUY","graham_confidence":"High","market_confidence":"High","graham_thesis":"Enterprise software with 19% revenue growth, 16.5% ROIC, 0.71脙聴 net debt/EBITDA, and 29% margin of safety at 13.9脙聴 P/E.","market_thesis":"19% revenue growth with 95% EPS acceleration supports 14脙聴 P/E multiple re-rating upward.","insight":"Enterprise software with 19% revenue growth, 16.5% ROIC, 0.71脙聴 net debt/EBITDA, and 29% margin of safety at 13.9脙聴 P/E.","score":110,"situation_type":"value_opportunity","scanned_at":"2026-05-12T17:00:07.047881+00:00","is_featured":false,"full_analysis":{"ai":null,"low52":130.89,"high52":219.69,"sector":"Technology","ticker":"PTC","country":"United States","peRatio":13.915385,"revenue":2739226000,"currency":"USD","fcfYield":5.1249586733624035,"marketCap":16715998208,"dualEngine":{"ctaSub":"Positive consensus 脗路 both engines agree","graham":{"why":["ROIC 16.5% well above 12% threshold; P/E 13.9脙聴 below 18 forward ceiling.","Gross margin 83.8%, operating margin 36.4%, net margin 26.8% 芒聙聰 pricing power evident.","Net debt/EBITDA 0.71脙聴 and interest coverage 12.9脙聴 indicate fortress balance sheet."],"risks":["PEG 1.61 suggests EPS growth (95%)